sentences: Ma olen pannud kõik oma tööd teisele päevale edasi.
Ta on pannud suure panuse selle projekti.
Nad on pannud kirja lepingu tingimused.
context: The word 'pannud' is the past tense of the Estonian verb 'panema', which means to put or place something somewhere. It is commonly used in everyday conversations to describe the act of putting or placing an object in a specific location.
